value.value: つやのある皮膚
skin with a glossy or glistening appearance
油っこい皮膚
skin secreting an unusually high amount of oil, resulting in a glossy, shiny appearance
締まった皮膚
skin has a taut, stretched appearance
薄い皮膚
reduced thickness of the outer protective layer of the body
厚い皮膚
greater thickness of the outer protective layer of the body
半透明の皮膚
skin that is more transparent to light than normal
感光性の皮膚
abnormally heightened reactivity of the skin to sunlight
照射感受性の皮膚
increased incidence of aberrant or damaged cells due to irradiation induced genotoxic damage
照射耐性の皮膚
decreased incidence of aberrant or damaged cells due to irradiation induced genotoxic damage
疱疹
accumulation of fluid- filled thin walled structures under the epidermis or within the epidermis
突発性皮膚潰瘍
unpredictable appearance of skin lesions, usually with inflammation
厚い皮膚の隆起
long raised strips of skin, usually aligned to the proximal-distal axis
しわのよった皮膚
irregular folds and/or indentations on the skin
皮膚傷害
focal pathological and/or inflammatory changes characterized by alteration in the size, shape and organization of the cellular components of the skin
皮膚細胞数の異常
greater than or fewer than the expected numbers of cells in the cutis
皮膚の肥厚
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the skin, typically resulting in increased thickness
皮膚の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the skin, typically resulting in decreased size
表皮層の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the superficial epithelial portion of the skin
表皮の欠如
missing the epidermal cell layer in the skin
薄い表皮
reduced thickness of the superficial epithelial portion of the skin
厚い表皮
increase in the width of the epidermal cell layer in the skin
上皮のネクローシス
morphological changes resulting from pathological death of the epidermal layer of skin; usually due to irreversible damage
上皮萎縮

acquired diminution of the size of epidermal layer of the skin, associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
上皮肥厚
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the epidermis, typically resulting in increased thickness
ケラチノサイトアポトーシス異常

aberrant programmed cell death or anomaly in the number of the cells of the epidermis that produce keratin in the process of differentiating into the dead and fully keratinized cells of the stratum corneum
上皮剥離
shedding of the cuticle of the epidermis in scales or shreds
表皮基底細胞層の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the deepest layer of the epidermis, which is composed of dividing stem cells and anchoring cells
表皮基底層の欠如
absence of the deepest layer of the epidermis, which is composed of dividing stem cells and anchoring cells
基底上層の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the suprabasal layer of the epidermis
基底上層の欠如
absence of the suprabasal layer of the skin
基底上層の組織崩壊
derangement of the pattern of the suprabasal layer of the skin
有棘層の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the layer of polyhedral cells in the epidermis; shrinkage and adhesion of these cells gives a spiny or prickly appearance
有棘細胞の巨大化
increased size of the immature keratinocytes of the spinous layer of the epidermis
表皮有棘層の菲薄化
reduced thickness of the stratum spinosum; the polyhedral cell layer
表皮顆粒層の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the layer of flattened cells containing basophilic granules of keratohyalin and lying just above the stratum spinosum (spiny layer) of the epidermis
表皮角化層の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the outer layer of the epidermis, consisting of several layers of flat keratinized non-nucleated cells
表皮角化層の欠如
absence of the outer layer of the epidermis, composed of several layers of keratinized non-nucleated cells
角質増殖
thickening of the horny layer of the epidermis
真皮層の形態異常
any structural anomaly or atypical condition of the dermal layer of the skin
薄い真皮層
reduced thickness of the dermis
厚い真皮層
increased depth of the dermis
真皮への混合性細胞浸潤
gradual accumulation of mixed cell types in the dermis that are not normally found there
真皮の嚢胞
presence of one or more abnormal membranous sacs in the dermis
真皮表層の細胞過形成
increased cell density of the superficial layer
体高異常
any anomaly in the shoulder to floor distance compared to controls
体高の増加
increased shoulder to floor distance compared to controls
体高の減少
decreased shoulder to floor distance compared to controls
体長異常
any anomaly in the measure of the head and trunk (head, thorax and abdomen) in the rostral-caudal direction
体長の増加
increased measure of the head and trunk (head, thorax and abdomen) in the rostral-caudal direction
体長の減少
decreased measure of the head and trunk (head, thorax and abdomen) in the rostral-caudal direction
